column2: NIB Stonehenge Anthology Board Game w/ Expansion
column3: Stonehenge: An Anthology Board Game + Stonehenge Nocturne: An Anthology Board Game Expansion  Publisher: Titanic Games (Paizo Publishing)  Designers: Richard Borg, James Ernest, Bruno Faidutti, Richard Garfield, Mike Selinker, Klaus-Jurgen Wrede, Bruno Cathala and Serge Laget, Andrew Looney  Description from the manufacturer:  Stonehenge has always been a mystery, its original purpose lost in time. Titanic Games asks the question: what would five world-class game designers make of such a location if they were the ones to discover it?  Titanic Games presents the world's first Anthology Board GameT. We gathered together five talented game designers and gave each of them the same board and pieces. Five unique designers resulted in five unique games: an Arthurian showdown by Richard Borg, a monumental fire sale by James Ernest, a druidic election by Bruno Faidutti, a magical convocation by Richard Garfield, and an alien chariot race by Mike Selinker.  Stonehenge contains:   One rulebook with five games   One game board   One deck of 65 cards   Five plastic trilithons  50 plastic disks   50 plastic bars   Six plastic pawns  Item Condition  Both items are new/sealed in original shrink wrap.  Shipping Info  This listing purchase offers PENNY SHIPPING! For just ONE PENNY added to the cost of your winning bid, you can have this item shipped to your door!    Packages weighing less than 1lb are shipped using Mail Innovations with an end delivery by USPS if the invoiced value is less than $100. Other packages are shipped via FedEx or other major carrier.

column3: High School Musical 3: Senior Year   New / Sealed  Product Description    It's time to celebrate as Disney's phenomenal HIGH SCHOOL MUSICAL hits new heights in HIGH SCHOOL MUSICAL 3: SENIOR YEAR! Fresh from the big screen, this motion picture extravaganza delivers nonstop entertainment from start to finish! It's almost graduation day for high school seniors Troy, Gabriella, Sharpay, Chad, Ryan and Taylor and the thought of heading off in separate directions after leaving East High has these Wildcats thinking they need to do something they'll remember forever. Together with the rest of the Wildcats, they stage a spring musical reflecting their hopes and fears about the future and their unforgettable experiences growing up together. But with graduation approaching and college plans in question, what will become of the dreams, romances and friendships of East High's senior Wildcats? Find out what happens to all your favorite characters in the big screen musical sensation, HIGH SCHOOL MUSICAL 3: SENIOR YEAR! It's a fabulous celebration the whole family will love! Bonus features include: Theatrical Version Of The Movie, Cast Goodbyes The Cast Of HSM 3 Bids An Emotional Farewell To East High      Product details      Actors: Zac Efron, Vanessa Hudgens, Corbin Bleu, Oleysa Rulin, Ashley Tisdale  Directors: Kenny Ortega  Format: Multiple Formats, AC-3, Color, Dolby, NTSC, Subtitled, Widescreen  Language: English (Dolby Digital 5.1), French (Unknown), Spanish (Unknown)  Subtitles: French, Spanish  Region: Region 1 (U.S. and Canada only. column2: Home Improvement: Season 8 DVD New Sealed
column3: Home Improvement: Season 8 DVD  New Sealed  Amazon.com  In its eighth and final season, classic sitcom Home Improvement holds up pretty well. Sure, plenty of recurring bits have gone stale--one imagines that star Tim Allen is looking forward to the day when he'll never have to grunt again, and hiding the face of neighbor Wilson (Earl Hindman) seems more like an obligatory chore than an entertaining game--but when the show focuses on the sitcom bedrock of marriage and family, it's not only still funny but sometimes even moving. The centerpiece of the whole season is a two-part episode that starts with an abundance of jokes about Tim's discomfort with female biology--then takes a jolting turn with the revelation that Jill (Patricia Richardson) has to get a hysterectomy. What follows is both comic and refreshingly honest as it captures Jill's anger and frustration, as well as a quietly touching portrait of how spouses support each other in times of trouble. Polly Holiday (Flo on Alice) boosts this episode with a strong appearance as Jill's mother.    The rest of the season goes up and down, suffering from some pointless celebrity appearances (Morgan Fairchild, Jay Leno, Oprah Winfrey, magicians Penn & Teller) and stunt-casting (Playboy playmate Jenny McCarthy as a mechanic Tim flirts with), and the departure of Jonathan Taylor Thomas (whose teen heartthrob career never quite launched) throws off the long-established family dynamic. But even otherwise rote episodes have satisfyingly funny moments (in a Halloween episode, there's a nice bit of slapstick when Tim, dressed as a flying monkey from The Wizard of Oz, can't get his wings through a doorway). The comfortable interplay among the seasoned cast ensures that longtime fans will find much to enjoy. The extras include some brief interviews, a blooper reel, and a retrospective special. --Bret Fetzer      Product details      Actors: Tim Allen  Format: Multiple Formats, Box set, Color, NTSC  Language: English (Dolby Digital 2.0 Stereo)  Region: Region 1 (U.S. and Canada only. Our Commitment:  At Goodwill Industries of North Louisiana, we want you to be completely satisfied with your purchase. We do our best to accurately describe and photograph our listings. Unless otherwise stated, items are not officially appraised, certified or authenticated. All weights and measurements are approximate and to the best of our knowledge. Before placing your bid, we strongly suggest that you read our Bidder Agreement. All Items are sold AS IS...AS FOUND Please note: Although we try our best to list as much information as we can about the items we sell, buyer be aware that all items are in pre-owned condition and also contain many unseen flaws/imperfections in addition to the information listed here. Please keep this in mind when shopping with us and ask all questions prior to placing a bid.  Payments    PayPal payments via the Shopgoodwill website are the only form of payment we accept, no exceptions.  Payment must be received within 7 days of the end of the auction  Items left unpaid for more than 10 days after auction ends will be re-listed.    Shipping    Please be aware of shipping charges before placing a bid.  We handle requests for combined shipping on a case-by-case basis; please use the 'Contact Customer Service' link provided for information prior to bidding or payment. We reserve the right to refuse the combination of any orders at our discretion.  USPS Media Mail is utilized strictly for books and media only, per carrier rules.  All other orders, as well as restricted items (such as liquids) will ship FedEx.  Minimum shipping weight is 1 pound, items utilizing FedEx or greater than 1728 cubic inches are shipped according to dimensional weight per carrier rules.  Insurance and Signature Confirmation - Buyer must email a request prior to making payment. We will then edit the order, adding the additional fees to the total.  We apologize, but if your package is damaged or lost, we will not be able to issue a refund unless your package was insured. We strongly recommend insurance on all breakable items. Photos will be required before a refund will be considered.  If an item is returned to us as undeliverable/unclaimed, it is the buyer's responsibility to contact us within 14 days and pay the additional postage to mail it again, otherwise items returned to us will be considered a donation and will be re-listed at our discretion.  Items will be shipped within 5 business days after payment.    Local Pickup    LOCAL PICKUP ORDERS: NO HANDLING FEES.  When you choose to pick up your order, the website will automatically remove both the shipping and the HANDLING fees, bringing them both to $0.00.  Pick up hours are 9:00am - 6:00pm Tuesday through Saturday.  Items paid by PayPal may be picked up the same day, once the transaction is verified.  ALL payments must be made through the Shopgoodwill.com website; we have no way to process payments at our location.  Local pick up items not claimed within 30 days will be re-listed, without notice and considered a donation    Handling    A minimum handling fee of $1.00 not to exceed $20.00 will appear at checkout. This fee applies ONLY to orders that are being shipped. There are no handling fees for local pick up. The exception to our maximum handling fee of $20.00 would be certain items that are very fragile, over-sized, irregularly shaped, and/or heavy may be subject to an increased handling fee. These fees, along with your purchase, help to support our mission.    Returns    All returns are potentially subject to a 10 Restocking Fee.  Returns will be accepted only with prior authorization and under the terms stated in the Return Policy.  Upon receipt of your item, we will refund the final bid amount minus restocking fee if applicable.  Bulk Jewelry Grab Bags/Boxes, Bulk Currency Lots, and Bulk Lego & Mini-Figures lots will NOT be accepted for return.    Customer Service    Customer Service: Our staff will make every effort to respond to your questions within 48 hours. Our customer service desk is open 9:00am - 6:00pm Tuesday through Saturday, CST. Please use the 'Contact Customer Service' link provided or call 318-629-5982. We will get back to you.  Please Visit Our Website to learn more about Goodwill Industries of North Louisiana.    Seller Contact Information:  8100 Jump Run  Shreveport LA 71115  Phone 318-629-5982     Return Policy: Merchandise is sold As Is. Returns will only be accepted with prior authorization and under the terms stated in this Return Policy. If you have questions regarding the quality or authenticity of this item please contact Goodwill Industries of North Louisiana, Inc. prior to placing your bid. Items may be returned within seven (7) days of receipt if the merchandise was damaged during shipping or if there was a major distortion in the description. Returns will not be accepted without prior authorization. PLEASE NOTE THAT WE DO NOT REFUND SHIPPING AND HANDLING CHARGES. Items selected for pick up from the seller must be picked up within thirty (30) days from the close of the auction. Items not picked up from the seller within thirty (30) days from the close of the auction will be resold with no further notice. There are no refunds for items that are resold in these circumstances.                                                              Goodwill Industries of North Louisiana, Inc. is a 501(c)(3) not-for-profit agency that serves people with disabilities and other barriers to employment.  For items shipped within LA, add 4 state sales tax. Save shipping by picking up orders (handling fee and 8.6 state & local sales tax apply).     Thanks for Supporting Goodwill Industries of North Louisiana.   -Improving People’s Lives through the Power of Work!

Our Commitment:  At Goodwill Industries of North Louisiana, we want you to be completely satisfied with your purchase. We do our best to accurately describe and photograph our listings. Unless otherwise stated, items are not officially appraised, certified or authenticated. All weights and measurements are approximate and to the best of our knowledge. Before placing your bid, we strongly suggest that you read our Bidder Agreement. All Items are sold AS IS...AS FOUND Please note: Although we try our best to list as much information as we can about the items we sell, buyer be aware that all items are in pre-owned condition and also contain many unseen flaws/imperfections in addition to the information listed here. Please keep this in mind when shopping with us and ask all questions prior to placing a bid.  Payments    PayPal payments via the Shopgoodwill website are the only form of payment we accept, no exceptions.  Payment must be received within 7 days of the end of the auction  Items left unpaid for more than 10 days after auction ends will be re-listed.    Shipping    Please be aware of shipping charges before placing a bid.  We handle requests for combined shipping on a case-by-case basis; please use the 'Contact Customer Service' link provided for information prior to bidding or payment. We reserve the right to refuse the combination of any orders at our discretion.  USPS Media Mail is utilized strictly for books and media only, per carrier rules.  All other orders, as well as restricted items (such as liquids) will ship FedEx.  Minimum shipping weight is 1 pound, items utilizing FedEx or greater than 1728 cubic inches are shipped according to dimensional weight per carrier rules.  Insurance and Signature Confirmation - Buyer must email a request prior to making payment. We will then edit the order, adding the additional fees to the total.  We apologize, but if your package is damaged or lost, we will not be able to issue a refund unless your package was insured. We strongly recommend insurance on all breakable items. Photos will be required before a refund will be considered.  If an item is returned to us as undeliverable/unclaimed, it is the buyer's responsibility to contact us within 14 days and pay the additional postage to mail it again, otherwise items returned to us will be considered a donation and will be re-listed at our discretion.  Items will be shipped within 5 business days after payment.    Local Pickup    LOCAL PICKUP ORDERS: NO HANDLING FEES.  When you choose to pick up your order, the website will automatically remove both the shipping and the HANDLING fees, bringing them both to $0.00.  Pick up hours are 9:00am - 6:00pm Tuesday through Saturday.  Items paid by PayPal may be picked up the same day, once the transaction is verified.  ALL payments must be made through the Shopgoodwill.com website; we have no way to process payments at our location.  Local pick up items not claimed within 30 days will be re-listed, without notice and considered a donation    Handling    A minimum handling fee of $1.00 not to exceed $20.00 will appear at checkout. This fee applies ONLY to orders that are being shipped. There are no handling fees for local pick up. The exception to our maximum handling fee of $20.00 would be certain items that are very fragile, over-sized, irregularly shaped, and/or heavy may be subject to an increased handling fee. These fees, along with your purchase, help to support our mission.    Returns    All returns are potentially subject to a 10 Restocking Fee.  Returns will be accepted only with prior authorization and under the terms stated in the Return Policy.  Upon receipt of your item, we will refund the final bid amount minus restocking fee if applicable.  Bulk Jewelry Grab Bags/Boxes, Bulk Currency Lots, and Bulk Lego & Mini-Figures lots will NOT be accepted for return.    Customer Service    Customer Service: Our staff will make every effort to respond to your questions within 48 hours. Our customer service desk is open 9:00am - 6:00pm Tuesday through Saturday, CST. Please use the 'Contact Customer Service' link provided or call 318-629-5982. We will get back to you.  Please Visit Our Website to learn more about Goodwill Industries of North Louisiana.    Seller Contact Information:  8100 Jump Run  Shreveport LA 71115  Phone 318-629-5982     Return Policy: Merchandise is sold As Is. Returns will only be accepted with prior authorization and under the terms stated in this Return Policy. If you have questions regarding the quality or authenticity of this item please contact Goodwill Industries of North Louisiana, Inc. prior to placing your bid. Items may be returned within seven (7) days of receipt if the merchandise was damaged during shipping or if there was a major distortion in the description. Returns will not be accepted without prior authorization. PLEASE NOTE THAT WE DO NOT REFUND SHIPPING AND HANDLING CHARGES. Items selected for pick up from the seller must be picked up within thirty (30) days from the close of the auction. Items not picked up from the seller within thirty (30) days from the close of the auction will be resold with no further notice. There are no refunds for items that are resold in these circumstances.                                                              Goodwill Industries of North Louisiana, Inc. is a 501(c)(3) not-for-profit agency that serves people with disabilities and other barriers to employment.  For items shipped within LA, add 4 state sales tax. Save shipping by picking up orders (handling fee and 8.6 state & local sales tax apply).     Thanks for Supporting Goodwill Industries of North Louisiana.   -Improving People’s Lives through the Power of Work!

column2: Home Improvement: Season 8 DVD New Sealed
column3: Home Improvement: Season 8 DVD  New Sealed  Amazon.com  In its eighth and final season, classic sitcom Home Improvement holds up pretty well. Sure, plenty of recurring bits have gone stale--one imagines that star Tim Allen is looking forward to the day when he'll never have to grunt again, and hiding the face of neighbor Wilson (Earl Hindman) seems more like an obligatory chore than an entertaining game--but when the show focuses on the sitcom bedrock of marriage and family, it's not only still funny but sometimes even moving. The centerpiece of the whole season is a two-part episode that starts with an abundance of jokes about Tim's discomfort with female biology--then takes a jolting turn with the revelation that Jill (Patricia Richardson) has to get a hysterectomy. What follows is both comic and refreshingly honest as it captures Jill's anger and frustration, as well as a quietly touching portrait of how spouses support each other in times of trouble. Polly Holiday (Flo on Alice) boosts this episode with a strong appearance as Jill's mother.    The rest of the season goes up and down, suffering from some pointless celebrity appearances (Morgan Fairchild, Jay Leno, Oprah Winfrey, magicians Penn & Teller) and stunt-casting (Playboy playmate Jenny McCarthy as a mechanic Tim flirts with), and the departure of Jonathan Taylor Thomas (whose teen heartthrob career never quite launched) throws off the long-established family dynamic. But even otherwise rote episodes have satisfyingly funny moments (in a Halloween episode, there's a nice bit of slapstick when Tim, dressed as a flying monkey from The Wizard of Oz, can't get his wings through a doorway). The comfortable interplay among the seasoned cast ensures that longtime fans will find much to enjoy. The extras include some brief interviews, a blooper reel, and a retrospective special. --Bret Fetzer      Product details        Actors: Tim Allen  Format: Multiple Formats, Box set, Color, NTSC  Language: English (Dolby Digital 2.0 Stereo)  Region: Region 1 (U.S. and Canada only. Pick up hours are 9:00am - 6:00pm Tuesday through Saturday.  Items paid by PayPal may be picked up the same day, once the transaction is verified.  ALL payments must be made through the Shopgoodwill.com website; we have no way to process payments at our location.  Local pick up items not claimed within 30 days will be re-listed, without notice and considered a donation    Handling    A minimum handling fee of $1.00 not to exceed $20.00 will appear at checkout. This fee applies ONLY to orders that are being shipped. There are no handling fees for local pick up. The exception to our maximum handling fee of $20.00 would be certain items that are very fragile, over-sized, irregularly shaped, and/or heavy may be subject to an increased handling fee. These fees, along with your purchase, help to support our mission.    Returns    All returns are potentially subject to a 10 Restocking Fee.  Returns will be accepted only with prior authorization and under the terms stated in the Return Policy.  Upon receipt of your item, we will refund the final bid amount minus restocking fee if applicable.  Bulk Jewelry Grab Bags/Boxes, Bulk Currency Lots, and Bulk Lego & Mini-Figures lots will NOT be accepted for return.    Customer Service    Customer Service: Our staff will make every effort to respond to your questions within 48 hours. Our customer service desk is open 9:00am - 6:00pm Tuesday through Saturday, CST. Please use the 'Contact Customer Service' link provided or call 318-629-5982. We will get back to you.  Please Visit Our Website to learn more about Goodwill Industries of North Louisiana.    Seller Contact Information:  8100 Jump Run  Shreveport LA 71115  Phone 318-629-5982     Return Policy: Merchandise is sold As Is. Returns will only be accepted with prior authorization and under the terms stated in this Return Policy. If you have questions regarding the quality or authenticity of this item please contact Goodwill Industries of North Louisiana, Inc. prior to placing your bid. Items may be returned within seven (7) days of receipt if the merchandise was damaged during shipping or if there was a major distortion in the description. Returns will not be accepted without prior authorization. PLEASE NOTE THAT WE DO NOT REFUND SHIPPING AND HANDLING CHARGES. Items selected for pick up from the seller must be picked up within thirty (30) days from the close of the auction. Items not picked up from the seller within thirty (30) days from the close of the auction will be resold with no further notice. There are no refunds for items that are resold in these circumstances.                                                              Goodwill Industries of North Louisiana, Inc. is a 501(c)(3) not-for-profit agency that serves people with disabilities and other barriers to employment.  For items shipped within LA, add 4 state sales tax. Save shipping by picking up orders (handling fee and 8.6 state & local sales tax apply).     Thanks for Supporting Goodwill Industries of North Louisiana.   -Improving People’s Lives through the Power of Work!

column2: WowWee Fingerlings Baby Sloth Toy SEALED/UNOPENED
column3: WowWee Fingerlings Baby Sloth Toy  Measurements:  5  Condition:  SEALED/ UNOPENED    ***Condition Disclaimer***  This is a USED item donated to Goodwill of North Louisiana.   Please see images for further detail and ask any questions you may have before making a bid.     Note: Any testing of electronics for power and/or functionality will be mentioned within the listing above ONLY if applicable.  In some instances we may not have the necessary equipment to test certain electronics therefore these will be auctioned off AS-IS with no refunds.                                                                                                               Our Commitment:  At Goodwill Industries of North Louisiana, we want you to be completely satisfied with your purchase. We do our best to accurately describe and photograph our listings. Unless otherwise stated, items are not officially appraised, certified or authenticated. All weights and measurements are approximate and to the best of our knowledge. Before placing your bid, we strongly suggest that you read our Bidder Agreement. All Items are sold AS IS...AS FOUND Please note: Although we try our best to list as much information as we can about the items we sell, buyer be aware that all items are in pre-owned condition and also contain many unseen flaws/imperfections in addition to the information listed here. Please keep this in mind when shopping with us and ask all questions prior to placing a bid.  Payments    PayPal payments via the Shopgoodwill website are the only form of payment we accept, no exceptions.  Payment must be received within 7 days of the end of the auction  Items left unpaid for more than 10 days after auction ends will be re-listed.    Shipping    Please be aware of shipping charges before placing a bid.  We handle requests for combined shipping on a case-by-case basis; please use the 'Contact Customer Service' link provided for information prior to bidding or payment. We reserve the right to refuse the combination of any orders at our discretion.  USPS Media Mail is utilized strictly for books and media only, per carrier rules.  All other orders, as well as restricted items (such as liquids) will ship FedEx.  Minimum shipping weight is 1 pound, items utilizing FedEx or greater than 1728 cubic inches are shipped according to dimensional weight per carrier rules.  Insurance and Signature Confirmation - Buyer must email a request prior to making payment. We will then edit the order, adding the additional fees to the total.  We apologize, but if your package is damaged or lost, we will not be able to issue a refund unless your package was insured. We strongly recommend insurance on all breakable items. Photos will be required before a refund will be considered.  If an item is returned to us as undeliverable/unclaimed, it is the buyer's responsibility to contact us within 14 days and pay the additional postage to mail it again, otherwise items returned to us will be considered a donation and will be re-listed at our discretion.  Items will be shipped within 5 business days after payment.    Local Pickup    LOCAL PICKUP ORDERS: NO HANDLING FEES.  When you choose to pick up your order, the website will automatically remove both the shipping and the HANDLING fees, bringing them both to $0.00.  Pick up hours are 9:00am - 6:00pm Tuesday through Saturday.  Items paid by PayPal may be picked up the same day, once the transaction is verified.  ALL payments must be made through the Shopgoodwill.com website; we have no way to process payments at our location.
